detroits population has dropped from about 2 million in 1950 to 
about 1 million today the flight to outlying suburbs has left 
behind thousands of boardedup burnedout houses that attract drug 
dealers and other crime some fedup residents tired of waiting for 
city demolition crews have even torn down abandoned houses 
themselves 
though youngs opponents have avoided mention of it young also 
faces a paternity suit filed against him by annivory calvert a 
former assistant director in detroits department of public works 
who now lives in california 
young who is single at first denied the child was his but in 
may blood tests proved he was the father of ms calverts 
6yearold son joel loving the mayor is paying 200 a week in 
child support until the court sets a final amount 
