<TEXT>
businessman nestor rapanelli was 
sworn in saturday as the fifth economy minister in 3 months and he 
pledged to complete the austerity program of miguel roig who died 
only six days after taking office 
rapanelli 60 took his oath of office from president carlos 
menem in the same government house room where an allnight wake was 
held for roig whose death of a heart attack friday shook the 
beleaguered south american nation 
the new minister said he would continue the policies of roig 
in an effort to halt hyperinflation end argentinas worst recession 
in 173 years and stop the widespread hunger that produced food riots 
in may 
a voluntary price accord with businesses that would allow the 
government to coordinate wage increases will be signed on monday 
or tuesday rapanelli told reporters 
roig 68 had been negotiating the agreement at the time of his 
death 
in choosing rapanelli menem turned again to the giant bunge and 
born grain conglomerate where the new minister served as vice 
president as had roig until his retirement three years ago 
rapanelli is the right man to maintain our economic program 
said menem as he joined roigs family friends and other officials 
at the wake 
rapanelli has worked for bunge and born for 39 years he also is 
vice president of the institute for executive development in 
argentina and is a director of the foundation for latin american 
economic investigation 
he faces a formidable task in continuing the program outlined by 
roig who was sworn in july 8 following menems inauguration 
roig on sunday announced a 54 percent devaluation of the austral 
and raised statecontrolled utility prices by at least 200 percent 
the currency held firm against the dollar which argentines use 
as a hedge against inflation during the first three days of the 
week 
but on thursday the dollars value on the black market soared 
above 700 australs compared to the official rate of 650 following 
a series of rumors including one that roig might resign 
inflation grew by 1145 percent in june and projections for july 
are 200 percent or more unemployment stands at about 10 percent 
real wages have shrunk by an estimated 60 percent 
the economic crisis led to food riots in late may that claimed at 
least 14 lives 
thousands of argentines now receive daily meals at soup kitchens 
that were set up last month menem has estimated that 9 million of 
the countrys 30 million inhabitants are living at the edge of 
misery 
on saturday the government sent 140 tons of food to the northern 
provinces of chaco and tucuman for distribution among the needy 
rapanelli is the nations fifth economy minister since march 31 
the day juan sourrouille resigned after failing to stabilize the 
economy 
two other ministers juan carlos pugliese and then jesus 
rodriguez also failed to implement economic reforms under former 
president raul alfonsin whose radical civic union lost the may 14 
elections to menems peronist party 
roig was not a peronist nor is rapanelli and his appointment 
added substance to menems claims that his administration would be 
nonpartisan 
roig described by associates as a sevenpackaday cigarette 
smoker is survived by his wife two sons and four grandchildren 
