southern california 
its where the drought is hartigan said the pattern has 
shifted southwest but id have to say that almost all of the west 
with very few exceptions is still not entirely recovered from four 
years of drought 
as far east as nebraska where the impact of drought is more 
often seen in withering corn fields fire is taking its toll 
but overall the first assault of the 1989 fire season still 
pales in comparison with the memory of 1988 
about 12500 firefighters were in the field at the height of 
activity last week there were about 30000 during the first week of 
september last year including 5600 army and marine troops 
