harmony and reverence for human rights echoed 
saturday from the summit document adopted by leaders of seven 
democracies in a windowless room on the 35th floor of the grand 
arch frances newest national symbol 
on the bicentennial of the french revolution it was only natural 
that president bush and his six partners reaffirmed their commitment 
to freedom and democratic principles even as they pointedly urged 
china to cease its repression of prodemocracy forces 
but facing no immediate threats to their security or their 
economies the summiteers issued a mild communique 
it thundered at terrorists without identifying their supporters 
it skirted the oppressive hunger of the undernourished third 
world 
