of course were in the sun belt and in the south you get more 
ultraviolet exposure he said and because of the weather 
people tend to develop more of an outdoor lifestyle so skin cancer 
is a real problem 
he added that certain types of skin cancer can be fatal if not 
treated early and sun damage can also hasten the aging of the skin 
people who stay outside longer than the index suggests usually 
15 to 30 minutes on a sunny or partlycloudy day should cover up 
or apply sun screens phillips said 
he added that weather can fool people they equate heat with 
sunburn so they think august is going to be the peak in 
ultraviolet radiation he said in fact the ultraviolet rays peak 
in june and july then decline steadly to late december when the 
sun is farthest away from the northern hemisphere phillips said 
